13.14. We apply induction on $n$. For $n=1$, we obtain an obvious identity. The equality

$$
\begin{aligned}
2\left(a_{1}+\frac{a_{1} a_{2}}{2}+\frac{a_{1} a_{2} a_{3}}{4}+\ldots+\right. & \left.\frac{a_{1} a_{2} \ldots a_{n} a_{n+1}}{2^{n}}\right) \frac{\pi}{4}= \\
