\end{aligned}
$$

It is not difficult to verify that in reality, the plus sign is always taken, since the sign of the number $a_{1}+\frac{a_{1} a_{2}}{2}+\frac{a_{1} a_{2} a_{3}}{4}+\ldots+\frac{a_{1} a_{2} \ldots a_{n} a_{n+1}}{2^{n}}$ coincides with the sign of the number $a_{1}$. Now, using the induction hypothesis, we obtain the required identity.

